How to create a local wiki for a metabolic network in padmet format.

--- REQUIREMENT ---
Install php
Install Docker

--- IMAGE BULDING ---
In this folder, run the following command:
shell$ make build

--- WIKI DEPLOYMENT ---
/!\ 1 container = 1 wiki
1/ Create a containner
Now that the image is built, you need to run a container.
In this folder, run the following command:
shell$ make run name=TheNameOfYourContainer (ex: yourSpeciesName, default = default_wiki)

2/ Mediawiki setup from browser
from your browser go to the following link:
http://localhost:8888/wiki/mw-config/index.php
- Follow this setup instructions.
a/ Language: press Continue
b/ Enter the update key: 0880a534700be3f7
c/ Accepte conditions (continue)
d/ Database settings: innoDB, binary
e/ Name 
	Name of wiki: what you want, ex: ecoli_network.
	project namespace: same as the wiki name.
	Create an account with username = 'admin' , password = 123456789
	/!\ WARNING: always use this account with this password, those data are used by default for wikiManager.
	Select: i'm bored already, just install the wiki.
	At the end do not save the LocalSettings.php file, juste cancel.
Setup complete

3/ Last setup and loading the metabolic network
docker init name=TheNameOfYourContainer (ex: yourSpeciesName, default = default_wiki) pages_dir=wikiPageDirectory

--- miscellaneous---
*Start a container
shell$ docker start container_name

*Stop a container
shell$ docker stop container_name

* Enter inside a container
docker exec -ti container_name bash

* Delete all containers /!\
docker rm $(docker ps -a -q)

* Delete all images /!\ 
docker rmi $(docker images -q)

*Export a container
docker export my_container > my_container.tar

*Import a container
docker import /path/to/exampleimage.tgz
docker load < aureme-padmet3-img.tar.gz



